snippet: There were no signs that Ms. Kennedy had been drinking before she hanged herself in a barn behind her home in Bedford, N.Y.
abstract: Autopsy report shows that Mary R Kennedy, the estranged wife of Robert F Kennedy Jr, who committed suicide in their Bedford, NY, home, had traces of at least three antidepressant drugs in her system.
lead_paragraph: There were no signs that Ms. Kennedy had been drinking before she hanged herself in a barn behind her home in Bedford, N.Y.

headline.seo: Antidepressants Found in Mary Kennedy Autopsy
headline.main: 3 Antidepressants Found in Autopsy of Mary Kennedy
